<SRosenstein@cfr.org>

[A lot of "ifs." Wild and domestic birds die of many conditions
besides H5N1. We can only wait and see what emerges. In the meanwhile
there have been calls for calm in the region, reminiscent of the
concerned elderly character in "Dad's Army." In February 2006 there
was a local over-reaction in the lower Zambezi which resulted,
apparently, in hundreds of villagers killing their domestic poultry
and goats on the rumour of an avian flu outbreak in the country.
<http://www.irinnews.org/Avianflu.asp>
<http://news.monstersandcritics.com/health/article_1174834.php/WHO_calls_for_calm_amid_bird_flu_probe_in_Zambia>
<http://www.todayonline.com/articles/125746.asp>
